  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for xen",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for xen fixes the following issues:\n\n- CVE-2020-28368: Intel RAPL sidechannel attack aka PLATYPUS attack (bsc#1178591, XSA-351) \n- CVE-2021-3308: IRQ vector leak on x86 (bsc#1181254, XSA-360)\n- CVE-2021-28687: HVM soft-reset crashes toolstack (bsc#1183072, XSA-368) \n- L3: conring size for XEN HV's with huge memory to small (bsc#1177204).\n- kdump of HVM fails, soft-reset not handled by libxl (bsc#1179148)\n- openQA job causes libvirtd to dump core when running kdump inside domain (bsc#1181989).\n- Upstream bug fixes (bsc#1027519)\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
